-- int_deduped_returns.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate: one approved return per item (latest submission)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        return_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_date DESC, return_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason,
    status
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

-- int_items_with_returns.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate: items enriched with return status
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        oi.item_id,
        oi.order_id,
        oi.product_id,
        oi.quantity,
        oi.unit_price,
        CASE WHEN r.return_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }} oi
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} r
        ON r.item_id = oi.item_id
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    order_id,
    product_id,
    quantity,
    unit_price,
    is_returned
FROM source
```

-- int_products_with_category.sql
```sql
-- Intermediate: products with category, handling null categories
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        p.product_id,
        p.name,
        COALESCE(c.category_id, -1) AS category_id,
        COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
    FROM {{ ref('stg_products') }} p
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
        ON c.category_id = p.category_id
)
SELECT
    product_id,
    name,
    category_id,
    category_name
FROM source
```

-- fct_return_rates_by_category.sql
```sql
-- Fact: return rates aggregated by category
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        iwr.item_id,
        iwr.is_returned,
        ipc.category_name
    FROM {{ ref('int_items_with_returns') }} iwr
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_products_with_category') }} ipc
        ON ipc.product_id = iwr.product_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(SUM(is_returned)::NUMERIC / COUNT(*), 4) AS return_rate
FROM source
GROUP BY
    category_name
ORDER BY
    category_name
